Year = {1980},
Volume = {135},
Number = {1-2},
Pages = {89-93},
Abstract = {Observations on 2 natural and 1 artificial distylous populations of P.
   veris in Britain revealed high proportions of intramorph pollen on pin
   stigmas and moderate proportions of intermorph pollen on thrum stigmas.
   The average ratio of pin:thrum pollen production per flower was 2.4:1.
   Large amounts of pollen remained in dehisced anthers, perhaps reflecting
   low levels of pollinator activity. Population size and density had no
   clear effect on pollen flow patterns, which are asymmetrical for the 2
   morphs.},
