   rare bee of conservation concern. Epeoloides are cleptoparasites of the
   oil-collecting bees Macropis (Hymenoptera: Melittidae), which specialize
   on oil-producing species in the genus Lysimachia (Ericales:
   Primulaceae). We report on the first records of E. pilosulus in Manitoba
   in 95-years, and only the fifth through eighth specimens for Canada
   since 1960. Manitoban records of Macropis are also provided.},
